utilityPhraseEnglish1                     Hello everyone! My name is Pepper. I am what is called a humanoid robot. That means I was designed to look and move a little like you, humans!
utilityPhraseKinyarwanda1                 I have a head
utilityPhraseEnglish2                     I have a head
utilityPhraseKinyarwanda2                 Munkurikire
utilityPhraseEnglish3                     I have arms and hands
utilityPhraseKinyarwanda3                 Ahari ikindi gihe
utilityPhraseEnglish4                     and I can move around
utilityPhraseKinyarwanda4                 Muraho! Murakazaneza muri robotikisi lab. Nitwa pepa nkaba ndi robo ifasha mugutembereza abashyitsi.
utilityPhraseEnglish5                     so I can interact with the world in ways that feel familiar
utilityPhraseKinyarwanda5                 Wakwifuza gutemberezwa muri laboratwari?
utilityPhraseEnglish6                     I am part of a research project called Culturally-Sensitive Social Robotics for Africa. The idea behind that is to help robots like me learn how to communicate politely and sensitively with people in Africa. Not just with words, but also with gestures, expressions, and body language! This projecect is made possible thanks to a collaboration between Carnegie Mellon University Africa, here in Rwanda, and the University of the VitVatersrand, in South Africa.
utilityPhraseKinyarwanda6                 Umuryango uri hano
utilityPhraseEnglish7                     I hope you enjoyed this presentation. See you again soon
